{"title": "Conceptions of Divine Love", "description": "Conceptions of Divine Love was written in 1577.  St. Teresa wrote this with the idea of explaining certain words found in the Book of Canticles.  When her confessor read the title of her work, he ordered her to immediately burn it, which, of course, she did.  But one of her nuns had copied the first seven chapters, which was then published in 1612.  Here, Father John Dalton has translated only four of those chapters in 1852. (Summary by Ann Boulais)", "duration": 3553, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "1562", "name": "Saint Teresa of Avila"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt21/Conceptions_Divine_Love_1208.jpg", "copyright_year": "1852", "genres": ["Christianity - Commentary"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "TriciaG"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Joy Easton"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "Preface", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/conceptions_divine_love_ab_librivox/conceptionsofdivinelove_0_teresa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 187}, {"section": 1, "title": "Chapter I", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/conceptions_divine_love_ab_librivox/conceptionsofdivinelove_1_teresa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 846}, {"section": 2, "title": "Chapter II", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/conceptions_divine_love_ab_librivox/conceptionsofdivinelove_2_teresa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1418}, {"section": 3, "title": "Chapter III", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/conceptions_divine_love_ab_librivox/conceptionsofdivinelove_3_teresa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 543}, {"section": 4, "title": "Chapter IV", "readers": [3681], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/conceptions_divine_love_ab_librivox/conceptionsofdivinelove_4_teresa_64kb.mp3", "duration": 559}]}